\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b graeca} (Bory & Chaub.) R. Fernandes, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc. }{\b 64}: 74 (1971) ({\i Antirrhinum graecum} Bory & Chaub.): Branches longer and slenderer than in subsp. ({\b a}). Leaves acute, rather narrow, the uppermost and those of the branches lanceolate-sagittate, very small. Pedicels 2-6 times as long as subtending leaf.{\i  S. part of Balkan peninsula, Aegean region}.
