\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b elatine}: Main branches decumbent, weak, often rather sparsely hairy; secondary branches few or none. Leaves acute to mucronate, mostly hastate, but the uppermost sagittate. Pedicels glabrous except just below the flower, 3-6 times as long as the calyx in flower, up to 3 cm in fruit. Corolla 7-10 mm. 2n = 36.{\i  Throughout the range of the species except Portugal and parts of the Mediterranean region}.
\par

